Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the
@garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice
widthways into pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and carrot. Season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Fry until the beef has browned and
carrot is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as
it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, add the green beans and @egg noodle nest{125%g} to the pan of
boiling water.

Simmer until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the
noodles sticking together and keep the veg vibrant.

Once the beef mince has browned, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%min}
more.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @bulgogi sauce{150%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sriracha sauce{15%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.
Bring to the boil and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and green beans to the beef.

Toss to coat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a
splash of @?water{} if it's a little dry.

Share your bulgogi beef noodles between #bowls{}. Enjoy!